hnologies of measurement, such as calorimeters and social surveys, and technologies of wages and welfare, such as minimum wages, poor aid, and welfare programs. In looking at how we define and measure need, Vital Minimum raises profound questions about the authority of nature and the nature of inequality.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aBasic needs - France - History - 20th century. 0aBasic needszFrancexHistoryy19th century. 0aBasic needszFrancexHistoryy20th century. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh  ascience, scientific, politics, political, france, modern, contemporary, french, europe, european, western, needs, amateur, professional, 20th century, human, nature, economy, economics, labor, social studies, order, class, classism, organization, structure, inequality, equality, basics, self actualization, subsistence, scarcity, recycling, reproduction, rations, reform, wages, socialism, welfare.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z97831106904390 cprintz978022625156140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226251738423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226251738/original  a978-3-11-069043-9  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles